label.value: somatic cell of salivary gland body primordium

value.value: A(n) somatic cell that is part of a(n) salivary gland body primordium.

label.value: somatic cell of presumptive embryonic salivary gland

value.value: A(n) somatic cell that is part of a(n) presumptive embryonic salivary gland.

An intrinsic columnar neuron of the visual system whose cell body is located in the medulla cortex and that has a main projection making wide-field arborizations in the lamina. It expresses the transcription factor Fer2 (Ozel et al., 2021) and is cholinergic (Davis et al., 2020).
The section of the adult foregut epithelium inside the proventriculus that extends from the apex of the cardial valve to its widest point (King, 1988).

The section of the adult foregut epithelium inside the proventriculus that extends from the widest point of the cardial valve its neck (King, 1988). This section is characterized by a clear gap between the cuticular surface and the underlying epithelial cell membrane.

The section of the adult foregut epithelium inside the proventriculus that occupies the neck of the cardial valve (King, 1988). It is the distalmost segment of the foregut epithelium inside the proventriculus.

The section of the adult midgut epithelium inside the proventriculus that extends from the end of the foregut cuticle to the fold between the intermediate and outer layers of the proventriculus (King, 1988). This is the anteriormost segment of the midgut epithelium inside the proventriculus.
The section of the adult midgut epithelium inside the proventriculus that forms the anterior segment of the outer wall of the proventriculus (King, 1988).
The section of the midgut epithelium in the outer layer of the proventriculus that extends between the zones 5 and 6 (Zhu et al., 2024).
The section of the adult midgut epithelium inside the proventriculus which forms the distal outer layer as it tapers towards the ventriculus (King, 1988).

Epithelial cell of the first zone of the adult proventriculus epithelium (King, 1988). This a columnar cell with a broad apex in contact with the overlying cuticle. It tapers basally toward a narrow point that curves anteriorly. There are approximately 500 of these cells in the adult proventriculus (Zhu et al., 2024).

Epithelial cell of the second zone of the adult proventriculus epithelium (King, 1988). This is a columnar cell with irregular cytoplasmic extensions (narrow folds and microvilli) which project into the extracellular material beneath the overlying cuticle. Its basal end is slightly narrower than its apex and inclined posteriorly. There are approximately 600 of these cells in the adult proventriculus (Zhu et al., 2024).

Epithelial cell of the third zone of the adult proventriculus epithelium (King, 1988). These cells are shorter than the cells from the first and second zones, and are characterized by numerous mitochondria. They secrete the first layer of the peritrophic membrane (Zhu et al., 2024). There are approximately 450 of these cells in the adult proventriculus.

Epithelial cell of the fourth zone of the adult proventriculus epithelium (King, 1988). These cells are short to cuboidal columnar cells with long apical microvilli that project loosely into the proventriculus lumen. They secrete the second layer of the peritrophic membrane (Zhu et al., 2024). There are approximately 200 of these cells in the adult proventriculus.

Epithelial cell of the fifth zone of the adult proventriculus epithelium (King, 1988). These are very tall columnar cells. Their apical end is drawn out into a cytoplasmic peg which projects into the lumen. They secrete the third layer of the peritrophic membrane (Zhu et al., 2024). There are approximately 1600 of these cells in the adult proventriculus.

Epithelial cell of the intermediate zone between the fifth and sixth zones of the adult proventriculus epithelium (Zhu et al., 2024). Along with cells from the sixth zone, they secrete the fourth layer of the peritrophic membrane. There are approximately 200 of these cells in the adult proventriculus.

Epithelial cell of the sixth zone of the adult proventriculus epithelium (King, 1988). These are cuboidal cells characterized by short, straight, closely packed microvilli and an irregularly infolded basal membrane. They secrete the fourth layer of the peritrophic membrane, as well as digestive enzymes (Zhu et al., 2024). There are approximately 700 of these cells in the adult proventriculus.
Olfactory intermediate sensillum of antennal segment 3 that houses the dendrites of three olfactory receptor neurons, expressing Or2a, Or19a and Or43a (Grabe et al., 2016).

definition.value: Reclassified from trichoid to intermediate by fluorescence-guided single sensillum recording (FG-SSR) (Lin and Potter, 2015; https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1373-1705). Dweck et al. (2013) - FBrf0223680 refer to this as ai2, but show presence of three neurons with one expressing Or19a.

value.value: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or2a (FBgn0023523). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus DA4 medial compartment and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus DA4 medial compartment. Its dendrite transduces signals from intermediate sensillum ai3. The numbers of these neurons have been estimated to 27 in females and 22 in males (Grabe et al., 2016).

Large olfactory basiconic sensillum of the antenna that houses the dendrites of two highly-branched olfactory receptor neurons (Shanbhag et al., 1999), expressing Or59b and Or85a (Couto et al., 2005; Grabe et al., 2016). It has a pore size of about 50 nm and a pore density of about 19 pores per square micrometer (Shanbhag et al., 1999). There are more of these sensilla in females than males (Shanbhag et al., 1999; Grabe et al, 2016).

definition.value: Corresponds to LB-I of Shanbhag et al. (1999) based on number of neurons and increased number present in female than male.

value.value: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or59b (FBgn0034865). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus DM4 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus DM4. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal basiconic sensillum ab2. The numbers of these neurons have been estimated to 23 in females and 15.5 in males (Grabe et al., 2016).
Thin antennal basiconic sensillum innervated by the dendrites of two olfactory receptor neurons, expressing Or56a and Or7a (Couto et al., 2005; Gonzales et al., 2021).

Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or7a (FBgn0030016). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus DL5 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus DL5. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal basiconic sensillum ab4. The numbers of these neurons have been estimated to 24 in females and 21 in males (Grabe et al., 2016).

definition.value: Glomerulus listed as VM5v in Gonzales et al. (2021) - FBrf0250923, but DL5 is specified in Grabe et al. (2016) and Task et al. (2022) - FBrf0253272.

value.value: Basiconic olfactory sensillum of maxillary palp that is innervated by the dendrites of two ORNs. It is distinguishable from pb1 and pb2 by its odor response profile (Goldman et al., 2005) and the identity of the ORNs that innervate it (59c and 85d; Couto et al., 2005; Goldman et al., 2005).

Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or59c. Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral glomerulus VM7v and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral VM7v. Its dendrite transduces signals from maxillary palp basiconic sensillum pb3. There are approximately 29 of these cells in females and 31 in males, on each side (Grabe et al., 2016).
Small antennal basiconic sensillum innervated by the dendrites of two olfactory receptor neurons, expressing Or43b and Or9a (Couto et al., 2005; Grabe et al., 2016).

Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or9a (FBgn0030204). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus VM3 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus VM3. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal basiconic sensillum ab8. The numbers of these neurons have been estimated to 18 in females and 15 in males (Grabe et al., 2016).

definition.value: Antennal basiconic sensillum ab4 is bidendritic. According to Hallem et al., 2004, adult ORN 43b corresponds to the functionally defined ORN ab8A. We can therefore deduce that adult ORN 9a corresponds to ORN ab8B.

value.value: Olfactory trichoid sensillum of antennal segment 3 that houses the dendrites of ORNs Or47b and Or88a, with a subset additionally housing an ORN Or65a dendrite (Grabe et al., 2016; Gonzales et al., 2021). There are more of these sensilla in males than females (Grabe et al, 2016).

Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or65 (Or65a ; FBgn0041625, Or65b ; FBgn0041624, Or65c ; FBgn0041623). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus DL3 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus DL3. Its dendrite transduces signals from an antennal trichoid sensillum at4 (Couto et al., 2005; Grabe et al., 2016) that houses three neurons (Gonzales et al., 2021). It responds to the male pheromone cis-vaccenyl acetate (cVA) (van der Goes et al., 2007). It expresses sNPF (Carlsson et al., 2010). The numbers of these neurons have been estimated to 19.5 in females and 25.5 in males (Grabe et al., 2016).

A large olfactory basiconic sensillum of the antenna that houses the highly branched dendrites of four ORNs (Shanbhag et al., 1999), expressing Or42b, Or92a, Gr21a and Or10a (Grabe et al., 2016). It has a pore size of about 100 nm and a pore density of about 30 pores per square micrometer (Shanbhag et al., 1999). There are more of these sensilla in females than males (Grabe et al, 2016).

Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or10a (FBgn0030298) and the gustatory receptor Gr10a (FBgn0045502) (Fishilevich and Vosshall, 2005). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus DL1 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus DL1. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal basiconic sensillum ab1. There are approximately 38 of these cells in females and 24 in males, on each side (Grabe et al., 2016).

label.value: adult antennal lobe projection neuron DC1 adPN

value.value: Adult uniglomerular antennal lobe projection neuron from the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) lineage whose dendrites mainly innervate antennal lobe glomerulus DC1. This neuron is born from the 11th division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) during embryogenesis (Yu et al., 2010). There is around one of these per hemisphere, it fasciculates with the medial antennal lobe tract and it is cholinergic (Bates et al., 2020). Its boutons in the mushroom body calyx are widely distributed, mostly within the dorsal half (Li et al., 2020). It is the only uniglomerular projection neuron to receive input in DC1 (Li et al., 2020).

Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or13a (FBgn0030715). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus DC2 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus DC2. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal basiconic sensillum ab6. There are approximately 15 of these cells in females and 11 in males, on each side (Grabe et al., 2016).

label.value: adult antennal lobe projection neuron DM3 adPN

value.value: Adult uniglomerular antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage with dendrites that mainly innervate antennal lobe glomerulus DM3. Neurons of this class are born during the 18th division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) during embryogenesis (Yu et al., 2010). There is around one of these per hemisphere, it fasciculates with the medial antennal lobe tract and it is cholinergic (Bates et al., 2020).

Adult olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or19a (FBgn0041626) and Or19b (FBgn0062565). It innervates the antennal lobe glomerulus DC1 bilaterally, fasciculating with the antennal lobe commissure (Kaur et al., 2019). Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal intermediate sensillum ai3. The numbers of these neurons have been estimated to 27 in females and 22 in males (Grabe et al., 2016).

Small antennal basiconic sensillum innervated by the dendrites of two olfactory receptor neurons, expressing Or49a and Or67a (Couto et al., 2005; Grabe et al., 2016). There are more of these sensilla in females than males (Grabe et al., 2016).

Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or67a (FBgn0036009). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus DM6 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus DM6. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal basiconic sensillum ab10. The numbers of these neurons have been estimated to 18 in females and 10.5 in males (Grabe et al., 2016).

definition.value: Antennal basiconic sensillum ab4 is bidendritic. According to Hallem et al. (2004), adult ORN 49a corresponds to the functionally defined ORN ab10A, implying that adult ORN 67a corresponds to ORN ab10B.

label.value: adult antennal lobe projection neuron DP1m adPN

value.value: Adult uniglomerular antennal lobe projection neuron from the ad neuroblast lineage with dendrites that mainly innervate antennal lobe glomerulus DP1m. This is the first neuron born from the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) during embryogenesis (Yu et al., 2010). The axonal terminals in the lateral horn branch extensively and occupy large regions of this neuropil (Ai et al., 2013). There is one of these per hemisphere, it fasciculates with the medial antennal lobe tract and it is cholinergic (Ai et al., 2013; Bates et al., 2020).
Small antennal basiconic sensillum innervated by the dendrites of two olfactory receptor neurons, expressing Or69a and Or67b (Couto et al., 2005; Grabe et al., 2016).

Adult olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or67b (FBgn0036019). It innervates the antennal lobe glomerulus VA3 bilaterally, fasciculating with the antennal lobe commissure (Kaur et al., 2019). Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal basiconic sensillum ab9. The numbers of these neurons have been estimated to 24 in females and 17.5 in males (Grabe et al., 2016).

A large olfactory basiconic sensillum of the antenna that houses the dendrites of two highly-branched olfactory receptor neurons (Shanbhag et al., 1999), expressing Or22a and Or85b (Couto et al., 2005; de Bruyne and Baker, 2008; Grabe et al., 2016). It has a pore size of about 100 nm and a pore density of about 30 pores per square micrometer (Shanbhag et al., 1999).

definition.value: Corresponds to LB-II2 of Shanbhag et al. (1999) based on number of neurons and similar number present in female and male.

value.value: Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or22a (FBgn0026398) and Or22b (FBgn0026397). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus DM2 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus DM2. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal basiconic sensillum ab3. It expresses sNPF (Carlsson et al., 2010). There are approximately 8 of these cells on each side (Grabe et al., 2016).
Small antennal basiconic sensillum innervated by the dendrites of two olfactory receptor neurons, expressing Or67c and Or98a (Couto et al., 2005; Grabe et al., 2016).

Bilateral olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or67c (FBgn0036078). Its axon branches, with one branch innervating the ipsilateral antennal lobe glomerulus VC4 and the other fasciculating with the antennal commissure and innervating the contralateral antennal lobe glomerulus VC4. Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal basiconic sensillum ab7. There are approximately 14 of these cells in females and 12 in males, on each side (Grabe et al., 2016).

label.value: adult antennal lobe projection neuron DL5 adPN

value.value: Adult uniglomerular antennal lobe projection neuron of the ad neuroblast (ALad1) with dendrites that mainly innervate antennal lobe glomerulus DL5. This neuron is born from the 16th division of the neuroblast ALad1 (FBbt:00067346) during embryogenesis (Yu et al., 2010). There is around one of these per hemisphere, it fasciculates with the medial antennal lobe tract and it is cholinergic (Bates et al., 2020).
Trichoid sensillum of antennal segment 3 that houses one sensory dendrite, belonging to an olfactory receptor neuron Or67d (Grabe et al., 2016; Gonzales et al., 2021).

Adult olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses OR67d (FBgn0036080). It also expresses fruitless (Yu et al., 2010). It innervates the antennal lobe glomerulus DA1 bilaterally, fasciculating with the antennal lobe commissure (Kaur et al., 2019). Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal trichoid sensillum at1 (Couto et al., 2005; Grabe et al., 2016). It responds to the male pheromone cis-vaccenyl acetate (cVA) (van der Goes et al., 2007). It expresses sNPF (Carlsson et al., 2010). There are approximately 62 of these cells on each side (Grabe et al., 2016).

definition.value: Work by Fishilevich and Vosshall (2005), suggested that some neurons of the class also innervated glomerulus VA2, but subsequent work showed this result to be an due to expression of the Or67d-GAL4 line used in a different ORN class (Fishilevich and Vosshall, 2007).

value.value: Olfactory intermediate sensillum of antennal segment 3 that is innervated by olfactory receptor neuron Or83c and olfactory receptor neuron Or23a (Grabe et al., 2016). There are more of these sensilla in males than females (Grabe et al, 2016).

definition.value: Reclassified from trichoid to intermediate by fluorescence-guided single sensillum recording (FG-SSR) (Lin and Potter, 2015; https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1373-1705).

value.value: Adult olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or23a (FBgn0026395). It innervates the antennal lobe glomerulus DA3 bilaterally, fasciculating with the antennal lobe commissure (Kaur et al., 2019). Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal intermediate sensillum ai2. The numbers of these neurons have been estimated to 15 in females and 18 in males (Grabe et al., 2016).

Adult olfactory receptor neuron (ORN) that expresses Or69a (FBgn0041622). It innervates the antennal lobe glomerulus D bilaterally, fasciculating with the antennal lobe commissure (Kaur et al., 2019). Its dendrite transduces signals from antennal basiconic sensillum ab9. There are approximately 24 of these cells in females and 18 in males, on each side (Grabe et al., 2016).
